bib_record.title: Dissipative collisions in 16O + 27Al at Elab=116 MeV

free_txt: the Variable Energy Cyclotron
at Kolkata, India
Fission fragments contributions have
been obtained by fitting the energy distributions
with a Gaussian having centroid at the energies
obtained from Viola systematics of total kinetic
energies of mass-symmetric fission fragments duly
corrected for asymmetric factorcs.The fission
fragments and the Deep Inelastic components of the
fragment angular distributions have been obtained by
integrating the respective energy distributions
obtained.
The fragments were detected using
three solid state (Si-surface barrier) telescopes
(~12-mu-m dE, 300-mu-m E) mounted in one arm of the
91.5-cm scattering chamber.Typical solid angle
subtended by each detector was ~0.3 msr. A monitor
detector 300-mu-m Si surface barrier was placed in
the other arm of the scattering chamber for
normalization purpose. The telescopes were calibrated
using an elastically scattered 16O ion from Au target
and an alpha particle from Th-alpha source. Typical
energy resolution obtained for the elastic 16-O peak
was ~375 keV.
The systematic errors in the data, arising
from the uncertainties in the measurements of:
* the solid angle,
* target thickness, and
* the calibration of current digitizer
have been estimated to be 10%.
the Variable Energy Cyclotron
at Kolkata, India
The experiment was performed using a 116-MeV 16O ion
beam which was recently upgraded with electron
cyclotron resonance heavy-ion source.
Inclusive energy distributions for various
fragments (3<Z<7) were measured in the angular range
15 to 115 degree using three solid state detector.
The target used was 420 mu-g/cm**2 self-supporting 27Al
data were received from Dr. C.Bhattacharya
